\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 The\'a0parietal lobe\'a0is one of the four\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lobes_of_the_brain"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 major lobes}}\'a0of the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cerebral_cortex"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 cerebral cortex}}\'a0in the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 brain}}\'a0of\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mammal"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 mammals}}. The parietal lobe is positioned above the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temporal_lobe"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 temporal lobe}}\'a0and behind the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frontal_lobe"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 frontal lobe}}\'a0and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_sulcus"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 central sulcus}}.\
\
The parietal lobe integrates\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sensory_system"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 sensory}}\'a0information among various\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sensory_modality"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 modalities}}, including spatial sense and navigation ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proprioception"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 proprioception}}), the main sensory receptive area for the sense of touch ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mechanoreceptor"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 mechanoreception}}) in the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Postcentral_gyrus"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 somatosensory cortex}}\'a0which is just posterior to the central sulcus in the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Postcentral_gyrus"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 postcentral gyrus}},\super \strokec5  \nosupersub \strokec4 and the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Two-streams_hypothesis#dorsal_stream"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 dorsal stream}}\'a0of the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_system"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 visual system}}. The major sensory inputs from the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_skin"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 skin}}\'a0({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mechanoreceptor"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 touch}},\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thermoreceptor"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 temperature}}, and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nociceptor"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 pain}}\'a0receptors), relay through the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thalamus"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 thalamus}}\'a0to the parietal lobe.\
\
Several areas of the parietal lobe are important in\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Language_processing_in_the_brain"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 language processing}}. The somatosensory cortex can be illustrated as a distorted figure \'96 the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cortical_homunculus"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 homunculus}}\'a0({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin_language"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 Latin}}: "little man"), in which the body parts are rendered according to how much of the somatosensory cortex is devoted to them. The superior parietal lobule and inferior parietal lobule are the primary areas of body or spacial awareness. A lesion commonly in the right superior or inferior parietal lobule leads to\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hemineglect"}}{\fldrslt \strokec5 hemineglect}}.\
\
The parietal lobe plays important roles in integrating sensory information from various parts of the body, knowledge of numbers and their relations,\'a0and in the manipulation of objects. Its function also includes processing information relating to the sense of touch.\'a0Portions of the parietal lobe are involved with visuospatial processing.}